Please examine the following writeup. I want to add a chapter on "Equivalence Relations, Equivalence Classes, Congurence Arithmetic"

This chapter must leverage on the material already discussed without modifying any of the existing content.

First introduce the notion of a relation and its domain and range.

Then introduce the notion of an equivalence relation and give some interesting, non-trivial examples that **do not** involve divisors or remainders.

Next, introduce the concept of congruences, show that conguency mod n is an equivalence relation on the integers, describe the equivalence classes, and introduce congruence arithmetic.

---

