$$a^{4n+p} + b^{2n} - a^p - 1$$
is divisible by $m$ for all positive integers $n$.
\item Let $n,k$ be positive integers with $k$ odd. Show that the number
$$1 \underbrace{000 \ldots 00}_{nk-1 \ \text{zeroes}} 1$$
is divisible by 
$$1 \underbrace{000 \ldots 00}_{n-1 \ \text{zeroes}} 1.$$
