$$a^{2^m} + 1 \ \text{divides} \ a^{2^n} - 1.$$
\item Let $n,k$ be positive integers with $k$ odd. Let $a = 1^k + 2^k + ... + n^k$. By writing 
$$2a = (1^k + n^k) + (2^k + (n-1)^k) + \ldots + (n^k + 1^k),$$
or otherwise, prove that $2a$ is divisible by $n+1$. By writing 
$$2a = 2 + (2^k + n^k) + (3^k + (n-1)^k) + \ldots + (n^k + 2^k),$$
or otherwise, prove that $2a$ is not divisible by $n+2$, and consequently, $a$ is not divisible by $n+2$.
\item If $n$ is a positive integer, show that $13^n + 5$ is divisible by 6 but not by 12 or 14.
